criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Women older than or equal to 18 years;

          -  Have a pre-established complaint or diagnosis of any subtype of urinary incontinence;

          -  Not performing any other physiotherapeutic treatment for urinary incontinence;

          -  Did not initiate drug treatment or had a surgical procedure for urinary incontinence
             in the 6 months prior to the survey.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Diagnosis or signs and symptoms of neurological diseases;

          -  Obesity grade II or higher (BMI ≥35)

          -  Gestational period;

          -  Gynecological disease in progress;

          -  Initiate drug treatment for UI in the course of the research;

          -  Do not reach 80% of attendance in the treatment sessions;

          -  Prolapse of the pelvic organs degree greater than II;

          -  Known aortic aneurysm;

          -  Acute inflammatory phase of gastrointestinal or genito-urinary tract diseases;

          -  Any other contraindication to visceral manual therapy;

          -  Any other condition that may limit the performance of visceral manual therapy.
